            "dur": "1.458", 
            "start": "486.542"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "were to just evaluate\nthe function g of 2.", 
            "dur": "2.86", 
            "start": "488"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, you&#39;d look\nat this definition,", 
            "dur": "1.98", 
            "start": "490.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, when x equals 2, I use\nthis situation right over here.", 
            "dur": "3.42", 
            "start": "492.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it tells me, it&#39;s\ngoing to be equal to 1.", 
            "dur": "2.69", 
            "start": "496.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let me ask a more\ninteresting question.", 
            "dur": "1.99", 
            "start": "498.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Or perhaps a more\ninteresting question.", 
            "dur": "2.21", 
            "start": "500.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What is the limit as x\napproaches 2 of g of x.", 
            "dur": "7.22", 
            "start": "503.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Once again, fancy notation,\nbut it&#39;s asking something", 
            "dur": "2.789", 
            "start": "510.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "pretty, pretty, pretty simple.", 
            "dur": "2.061", 
            "start": "513.159"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s saying as x gets closer and\ncloser to 2, as you get closer", 
            "dur": "3.538", 
            "start": "515.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and closer, and this isn&#39;t\na rigorous definition,", 
            "dur": "2.041", 
            "start": "518.758"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we&#39;ll do that in future videos.", 
            "dur": "1.62", 
            "start": "520.799"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "As x gets closer and closer to\n2, what is g of x approaching?", 
            "dur": "5.631", 
            "start": "522.419"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if you get to 1.9, and\nthen 1.999, and then 1.999999,", 
            "dur": "5.16", 
            "start": "528.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and then 1.9999999, what\nis g of x approaching.", 
            "dur": "4.75", 
            "start": "533.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Or if you were to go from\nthe positive direction.", 
            "dur": "2.49", 
            "start": "537.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you were to say\n2.1, what&#39;s g of 2.1,", 
            "dur": "2.23", 
            "start": "540.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "what&#39;s g of 2.01, what&#39;s g of\n2.001, what is that approaching", 
            "dur": "5.37", 
            "start": "542.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as we get closer\nand closer to it.", 
            "dur": "2.05", 
            "start": "548.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And you can see it visually\njust by drawing the graph.", 
            "dur": "2.41", 
            "start": "550.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "As g gets closer\nand closer to 2,", 
            "dur": "3.1", 
            "start": "552.51"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and if we were to\nfollow along the graph,", 
            "dur": "2.74", 
            "start": "555.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we see that we\nare approaching 4.", 
            "dur": "2.21", 
            "start": "558.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Even though that&#39;s not\nwhere the function is,", 
            "dur": "2.37", 
            "start": "560.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the function drops down to 1.", 
            "dur": "1.91", 
            "start": "562.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The limit of g of x as x\napproaches 2 is equal to 4.", 
            "dur": "6.1", 
            "start": "564.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And you could even do this\nnumerically using a calculator,", 
            "dur": "2.6", 
            "start": "570.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and let me do that, because I\nthink that will be interesting.", 
            "dur": "4.63", 
            "start": "573.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So let me get the\ncalculator out,", 
            "dur": "1.625", 
            "start": "578.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "let me get my trusty TI-85 out.", 
            "dur": "3.435", 
            "start": "579.795"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So here is my calculator,\nand you could numerically", 
            "dur": "2.84", 
            "start": "585.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "say, OK, what&#39;s it\ngoing to approach", 
            "dur": "1.95", 
            "start": "588.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as you approach x equals 2.", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "590.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So let&#39;s try 1.94,\nfor x is equal to 1.9,", 
            "dur": "3.54", 
            "start": "593.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you would use this top\nclause right over here.", 
            "dur": "2.24", 
            "start": "597.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So you&#39;d have 1.9 squared.", 
            "dur": "4.52", 
            "start": "599.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so you get 3.61, well what\nif you get even closer to 2,", 
            "dur": "3.21", 
            "start": "604.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so 1.99, and once again,\nlet me square that.", 
            "dur": "5.45", 
            "start": "607.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well now I&#39;m at 3.96.", 
            "dur": "1.68", 
            "start": "612.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What if I do 1.999,\nand I square that?", 
            "dur": "4.305", 
            "start": "614.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m going to have 3.996.", 
            "dur": "1.92", 
            "start": "621.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Notice I&#39;m going\ncloser, and closer,", 
            "dur": "1.76", 
            "start": "623.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and closer to our point.", 
            "dur": "2.41", 
            "start": "625.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And if I did, if I\ngot really close,", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "627.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "1.9999999999 squared,\nwhat am I going to get to.", 
            "dur": "6.36", 
            "start": "629.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s not actually\ngoing to be exactly 4,", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "636.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "this calculator just\nrounded things up,", 
            "dur": "1.86", 
            "start": "638.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but going to get to a number\nreally, really, really, really,", 
            "dur": "2.5", 
            "start": "640.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "really, really, really,\nreally, really close to 4.", 
            "dur": "2.267", 
            "start": "642.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And we can do something from\nthe positive direction too.", 
            "dur": "2.333", 
            "start": "644.917"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it actually has\nto be the same number", 
            "dur": "1.708", 
            "start": "647.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when we approach from the below\nwhat we&#39;re trying to approach,", 
            "dur": "3.322", 
            "start": "648.958"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and above what we&#39;re\ntrying to approach.", 
            "dur": "2.42", 
            "start": "652.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if we try to 2.1\nsquared, we get 4.4.", 
            "dur": "5.32", 
            "start": "654.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If we do 2.", 
            "dur": "0.96", 
            "start": "660.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "let me go a couple\nof steps ahead,", 
            "dur": "1.89", 
            "start": "660.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "2.01, so this is much\ncloser to 2 now, squared.", 
            "dur": "5.05", 
            "start": "662.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now we are getting\nmuch closer to 4.", 
            "dur": "1.5", 
            "start": "667.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the closer we\nget to 2, the closer", 
            "dur": "2.29", 
            "start": "669.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it seems like\nwe&#39;re getting to 4.", 
            "dur": "1.52", 
            "start": "671.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So once again,\nthat&#39;s a numeric way", 
            "dur": "1.95", 
            "start": "673.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of saying that the\nlimit, as x approaches 2", 
            "dur": "3.93", 
            "start": "675.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "from either direction of g\nof x, even though right at 2,", 
            "dur": "3.51", 
            "start": "679.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the function is equal to 1,\nbecause it&#39;s discontinuous.", 
            "dur": "2.61", 
            "start": "682.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The limit as we&#39;re\napproaching 2,", 
            "dur": "1.75", 
            "start": "685.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we&#39;re getting closer, and\ncloser, and closer to 4.", 
            "dur": "3.823", 
            "start": "686.98"
        }
